dict.string: The Dock payload is designated by specifying com.apple.dock as the PayloadType. The Dock payload is supported on the user channel and, except for AllowDockFixupOverride, on all version of macOS. The key AllowDockFixupOverride is supported on macOS 10.12 and later.
Optional. A human-readable description of this payload. This description is shown on the Detail screen.
A human-readable name for the profile payload. This name is displayed on the Detail screen. It does not have to be unique.
A unique identifier for the payload, dot-delimited. Usually root PayloadIdentifier+subidentifier.
A reverse-DNS-style identifier for the specific payload. It is usually the same identifier as the root-level PayloadIdentifier value with an additional component appended.
The type of the payload, a reverse dns string.
A globally unique identifier for the payload. The actual content is unimportant, but it must be globally unique. In macOS, you can use uuidgen to generate reasonable UUIDs.
The version of the whole configuration profile.

The version number of the individual payload. A profile can consist of payloads with different version numbers. For example, changes to the VPN software in iOS might introduce a new payload version to support additional features, but Mail payload versions would not necessarily change in the same release.
This value describes the issuing organization of the profile, as displayed to the user.

Optional. A human-readable string containing the name of the organization that provided the profile. The payload organization for a payload need not match the payload organization in the enclosing profile.
Dock items in the Applications side that cannot be removed from the dock.
Optional. Dock items in the Applications side that cannot be removed from the dock.
The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. Information about a dock item.
Required. Label of a dock item.
Display name in the profile GUI of a dock item.
The type of the tile expressed as a number.
Required. The type of the tile expressed as a number. 3 = directory, 0 = URL, 1 = file.
Dock items in the Documents side that cannot be removed from the dock.
Optional. Dock items in the Documents side that cannot be removed from the dock.
The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. The type of the tile. Values may be file-tile, directory-tile, or url-tile. If you are unsure whether the file item is a file or a directory, set this key to file-tile.
Required. Information about a dock item.
Required. Label of a dock item.
Display name in the profile GUI of a dock item.
The type of the tile expressed as a number.
Required. The type of the tile expressed as a number. 3 = directory, 0 = URL, 1 = file.
Path to item relative to the current user's home directory.
Display directory as either a Folder or a Stack.
Optional. The tile size. Values must be in range 16 to 128.
Prevent user from changing tile size.
Optional. If true, the size slider will be disabled.
Set to true to turn on magnification.
Optional. If true, magnification is active.
Prevent user from changing the enable magnification setting.
Optional. If true, the magnification checkbox is disabled.
Largest magnification tile size in pixels.
Optional. THe size of the largest magnification. Values must be in range 16 to 128.
Prevent user from changing magnification size.
Optional. If true, the magnify slider is disabled.
Optional. Orientation of the dock. Values may be bottom, left, or right.
Optional. If true, the position is locked.
Transition effect to use when minimizing applications to the Dock.
Optional. Set minimize effect. Values may be genie or scale.
Prevent user from changing the minimization setting.
Optional. If true, the Minimize Using popup is disabled.
Set to true to minimize windows into application icons.
Optional. If true, enable the minimize-to-application feature.
Prevent user from changing the minimize windows into application icon setting.
Optional. If true, the minimize-to-application checkbox is disabled.
Minimize windows into application icon Checkbox Disable
Set to true to use launch animation.
Optional. If true, animate opening applications.
Prevent user from changing the animate opening applications setting.
Optional. If true, the Animate Opening Applications checkbox is disabled.
Set to true to automatically hide and show the dock.
Optional. If true, automatically hide and show the dock.
Automatically hide and show the Dock
Prevent user from changing the automatically hide and show the dock setting.
Optional. If true, the Automatically Hide checkbox is disabled.
Automatically hide and show the Dock checkbox disabled
Set to true to show an indicator below the application icon when an application is running.
Optional. If true, show the process indicator.
Set to true to show recent applications in the Dock.
If true, the three most recent applications will be shown in the Dock.
Whether these settings will merge with the user's existing Dock settings.

Optional. If true, the device will use the static-apps and static-others dictionaries for the dock and ignore any items in the persistent-apps and persistent-others dictionaries. If false, the contents will be merged with the static items listed first.
Remove non-static apps and documents from Dock
Prevent user from removing any item from or adding any item to the dock.
Optional. If true, the user cannot remove any item from or add any item to the dock.

If true, use the file in /Library/Preferences/com.apple.dockfixup.plist when a new user or migrated user logs in. The format of this file currently has no documentation. This option has no effect for existing users.

Optional. If true, use the file in /Library/Preferences/ com.apple.dockfixup.plist when a new user or migrated user logs in. The format of this file currently has no documentation. This option has no effect for existing users.

Optional. One or more special folders that may be created at user login time and placed in the dock. Values may be AddDockMCXMyApplicationsFolder, AddDockMCXDocumentsFolder, AddDockMCXSharedFolder, or AddDockMCXOriginalNetworkHomeFolder. The ”My Applications” item is only used for Simple Finder environments. The ”Original Network Home” item is only used for mobile account users.
Flag for the folder to be added by Managed Client.
